  "response": "As of 2023, Uber has made progress towards profitability, achieving positive adjusted EBITDA and net income in recent quarters. However, long-term global profitability remains uncertain due to:\n\n1. Challenges:\n- Regulatory issues in different markets\n- High driver compensation costs\n- Intense competition\n- Significant investment in technology and expansion\n\n2. Positive signs:\n- Diversification into delivery and freight services\n- Cost-cutting measures\n- Improved operational efficiency\n- Growing market share in ride-sharing and delivery\n\n3. Key factors for future profitability:\n- Continued cost management\n- Technological innovation\n- Autonomous vehicle development\n- Potential regulatory environment changes\n\nWhile Uber shows promise, sustained global profitability is not guaranteed and depends on multiple complex factors. The company continues to evolve its business model to improve financial performance.\n\nInvestors and analysts have varying opinions on Uber's long-term profitability potential, with some optimistic and others skeptical.",
